cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses a system for distributed training of deep learning models using idle compute of everyday electronic devices. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The system also involves data collection from diverse sources, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper introduces a reinforcement learning policy for training on heterogeneous clusters, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
